bnx2x_init_values_e1h.c
00001 /* init_ops array contains the list of operations needed to initialize the chip.
00002  *
00003  * For each block in the chip there are three init stages:
00004  * common - HW used by both ports,
00005  * port1 and port2 - initialization for a specific Ethernet port.
00006  * When a port is opened or closed, the management CPU tells the driver
00007  * whether to init/disable common HW in addition to the port HW.
00008  * This way the first port going up will first initializes the common HW,
00009  * and the last port going down also resets the common HW
00010  *
00011  * For each init stage/block there is a list of actions needed in a format:
00012  * {operation, register, data}
00013  * where:
00014  * OP_WR - write a value to the chip.
00015  * OP_RD - read a register (usually a clear on read register).
00016  * OP_SW - string write, write a section of consecutive addresses to the chip.
00017  * OP_SI - copy a string using indirect writes.
00018  * OP_ZR - clear a range of memory.
00019  * OP_ZP - unzip and copy using DMAE.
00020  * OP_WB - string copy using DMAE.
00021  *
00022  * The #defines mark the stages.
00023  *
00024  */
00025 #include <linux/version.h>
00026 #include <linux/module.h>
00027 #include <linux/pci.h>
00028 #include <linux/netdevice.h>
00029 #include <linux/delay.h>
00030 #include "bnx2x_compat.h"
00031 #include "bnx2x_init.h"
00032 #include "bnx2x.h"
